               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>This manuscript of two folios contains the 45th <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term> of the <title xml:lang="sa">Garuḍapurāṇa</title>. In his translation, M. N. Dutt has titled this chapter <quote>Characteristic marks of S'alagrama Stones</quote> (1908, iii); this title comes from the first verse of the <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term>, which states that it will deal with the characteristics of <term xml:lang="sa">śālagrāma</term> stone — <quote xml:lang="sa">prasaṅgāt kathayiṣyāmi śālagrāmasya lakṣaṇam</quote> (ed. Pandey, 60). However, in this manuscript, that line is omitted. Instead, the last few lines of the previous <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term> are used as an introduction, which urges the listener to worship <term xml:lang="sa">Viṣṇu</term> in his twenty-four forms. Thus, this single chapter, which lists the different manifestations (<term xml:lang="sa">mūrti</term>) of <term xml:lang="sa">Viṣṇu</term>, is re-contextualized as a self-contained text — it ends by, again, urging the listener to worship these different manifestations, which will result in the attainment of <term xml:lang="sa">dharma</term>, <term xml:lang="sa">artha</term>, <term xml:lang="sa">kāma</term>, and <term xml:lang="sa">mokṣa</term>.</p>
<p>Nevertheless, the completion statement at the end states <quote xml:lang="sa">iti gāruḍe vāsudevamūrttayaḥ</quote>, indicating that it is part of the <title xml:lang="sa">Garuḍapurāṇa</title>. This is the title that Filliozat gave to the manuscript — <quote>(Garuḍe) Vāsudevamurttaya</quote>.</p></summary>
                  
